# Project: BoostPlatform — Game Boosting Service

## Stack
- Next.js 15 (App Router) + TypeScript strict mode
- Tailwind CSS 3.4 + shadcn/ui (customized dark theme)
- Supabase (auth, DB, RLS, Realtime, Storage)
- Stripe + PayPal (unified payment interface)
- Zustand (client state) + TanStack Query v5 (server state)
- React Hook Form + Zod (forms + validation)
- Framer Motion (animations + page transitions)
- TanStack Table v8 (data tables with sorting, filtering, pagination)
- Tiptap (rich text editor for admin CMS)
- Recharts (charts and graphs)
- cmdk (command palette)
- Resend + React Email (transactional emails)

## Architecture
- Next.js 15 features: next.config.ts supported, async cookies(), turbopack dev
- /app/(storefront)/ → Public webshop (SSR for SEO)
- /app/(customer)/ → Customer dashboard (protected)
- /app/(worker)/ → Worker/booster dashboard (protected, role: worker)
- /app/(admin)/ → Admin panel (protected, role: admin/super_admin)
- /app/api/ → API routes (webhooks, checkout, CRUD, external API)
- /discord-bot/ → Separate Discord bot service (Node.js on VPS)
- /supabase/migrations/ → Database migrations (version controlled)

## GitHub & Deployment
- GitHub repo: https://github.com/master00J/Boosting
- Hosting: Vercel (auto-deploys on every push to main)
- **After every meaningful set of changes: commit and push to GitHub**
- The git repo lives inside `boost-platform/` — always run git commands from that directory
- Push command (PowerShell — use semicolons, NOT &&):
  `cd "C:\Users\j.ploegaerts\Desktop\coding stuff\new project\boost-platform"; git add .; git commit --trailer "Made-with: Cursor" -m "message"; git push origin main 2>&1`
- NEVER use HEREDOC (cat <<'EOF') — this is PowerShell, not bash. Use a simple -m "message" string.
- When using `git add` with specific files that contain parentheses in the path (e.g. `(admin)`), always quote the path: `git add "src/app/(admin)/..."`
- For multiple files with parentheses in paths, use `git add .` instead of listing files individually.
- The app is tested live on Vercel — always push so changes can be verified
- Root directory for Vercel: `boost-platform/`
- Never commit `.env.local` or any file with real secrets

